# CONTRACTRO - Romanian Contract Platform Transformation Tasks

**Goal**: Transform this lead generation platform into a superior Romanian contract management platform (competitor to econtracte.ro)

**Based on research of:**
- Current codebase: Laravel 12 + Wave SaaS + Filament Admin
- Competitor: econtracte.ro (features analyzed in detail)

---

## PHASE 1: DATABASE & CORE ARCHITECTURE (Foundation)

### 1.1 Database Schema Design
- [ ] Create `companies` table (multiple legal entities per user)
  - Fields: name, cui (CUI fiscal code), reg_com, address, phone, email, bank_account, logo, settings (JSON)
- [ ] Create `contracts` table
  - Fields: company_id, user_id, contract_type_id, contract_number, title, parties (JSON), content, status (draft/pending/signed/expired), signing_method, created_at, signed_at, expires_at, metadata (JSON)
- [ ] Create `contract_types` table
  - Fields: company_id, name, category, template, fields_schema (JSON), numbering_format, is_system_default
  - System types: service_contract, rental_contract, collaboration_contract, employment_contract, loan_contract, purchase_sale_contract
- [ ] Create `contract_templates` table
  - Fields: company_id, contract_type_id, name, content, variables (JSON), is_active, is_default
- [ ] Create `contract_parties` table
  - Fields: contract_id, party_type (client/provider/witness), name, email, phone, id_series, id_number, address, company_cui, is_signed, signed_at, ip_address, signature_data (JSON)
- [ ] Create `contract_signatures` table
  - Fields: contract_id, party_id, signature_method (sms/handwritten/digital), verification_code, verification_phone, signed_at, ip_address, user_agent, metadata (JSON)
- [ ] Create `contract_attachments` table
  - Fields: contract_id, file_name, file_path, file_type, size, uploaded_by, uploaded_at
- [ ] Create `contract_amendments` table (acte adiționale)
  - Fields: contract_id, amendment_number, title, content, status, created_by, created_at, signed_at
- [ ] Create `contract_tasks` table
  - Fields: contract_id, assigned_to, title, description, due_date, status, priority, completed_at
- [ ] Create `contract_notes` table
  - Fields: contract_id, user_id, note, is_internal, created_at
- [ ] Create `invoices` table
  - Fields: company_id, contract_id, invoice_number, series, client_name, client_cui, amount, vat_amount, total_amount, currency, issue_date, due_date, status, payment_date, items (JSON)
- [ ] Create `contract_numbering` table
  - Fields: company_id, contract_type_id, year, prefix, last_number, format, reserved_numbers (JSON)
- [ ] Create `document_templates` table
  - Fields: company_id, type (contract/invoice/amendment), name, content, variables, settings (JSON)
- [ ] Create `financial_reports` table (cached reports)
  - Fields: company_id, report_type, period_start, period_end, data (JSON), generated_at
- [ ] Create `user_permissions` table
  - Fields: user_id, company_id, permissions (JSON), role
- [ ] Create migration files for all tables
- [ ] Add indexes for performance (contract_number, status, company_id, created_at)

